A rage room? Denise. this is silly.

13
00:00:25.310 --> 00:00:27.070
Come on. it'll be fun.

14
00:00:27.080 --> 00:00:28.720
We get to smash a bunch of junk.

15
00:00:28.930 --> 00:00:30.460
- I don't know.
- Oh. Emily.

16
00:00:30.470 --> 00:00:31.860
We are doing this.

17
00:00:31.860 --> 00:00:33.290
When is the last time
you allowed yourself

18
00:00:33.290 --> 00:00:34.960
to feel angry?

19
00:00:34.960 --> 00:00:37.210
I mean. really angry. Never.

20
00:00:37.220 --> 00:00:39.270
Even after Eric asked you for the divorce.

21
00:00:39.270 --> 00:00:40.170
Just think of his face

22
00:00:40.170 --> 00:00:42.550
every time you smash
something to pieces.

23
00:00:42.560 --> 00:00:44.060
Okay. I'm in.

24
00:00:44.060 --> 00:00:45.580
(BELL RINGS)

25
00:00:45.580 --> 00:00:48.890
(GLASS SHATTERING)

26
00:00:48.900 --> 00:00:50.730
- Hm.
- Shall we?

27
00:00:50.730 --> 00:00:52.900
(BELL RINGING)

28
00:00:52.900 --> 00:00:55.260
(GRUNTS)

29
00:00:55.260 --> 00:00:56.690
Whoo! You're up!

30
00:00:58.080 --> 00:01:00.580
(CLINKING)

31
00:01:01.080 --> 00:01:02.530
I don't think this is working.

32
00:01:02.540 --> 00:01:04.600
Come on! You gotta reach down deep

33
00:01:04.600 --> 00:01:07.060
and find your rage!

34
00:01:07.060 --> 00:01:08.250
(LAUGHS)

35
00:01:10.940 --> 00:01:12.570
- Okay.
- Remember when you made

36
00:01:12.570 --> 00:01:15.710
that big anniversary dinner
and Eric didn't even show up?

37
00:01:15.710 --> 00:01:17.350
Didn't that piss you off?
(BANGING)

38
00:01:17.350 --> 00:01:19.570
Yes. I spent $400 on a sous-vide

39
00:01:19.580 --> 00:01:20.980
and boiled meat in a plastic bag.

40
00:01:20.980 --> 00:01:24.120
- Yeah. you did.
- Oh. Okay.

41
00:01:24.120 --> 00:01:25.460
That a girl!

42
00:01:25.460 --> 00:01:26.910
What about the time when he took

43
00:01:26.920 --> 00:01:28.430
that boys' trip up in Big Bear

44
00:01:28.440 --> 00:01:31.460
and he left you home alone
with a sick two-year-old?

45
00:01:31.470 --> 00:01:33.440
I was covered in puke and poop

46
00:01:33.440 --> 00:01:34.590
and he was at a ski lodge

47
00:01:34.590 --> 00:01:37.300
sipping bourbon and smoking cigars!

48
00:01:37.300 --> 00:01:39.260
And what about that thing he does

49
00:01:39.260 --> 00:01:42.000
where he barks like a
seal when he's having sex?

50
00:01:42.000 --> 00:01:45.830
I mean. what is that about?

51
00:01:48.310 --> 00:01:49.730
I never told you about that.

52
00:01:49.730 --> 00:01:51.770
Sure. you did. Ahh...

53
00:01:51.780 --> 00:01:54.030
I mean. you must have.
You tell me everything.

54
00:01:54.030 --> 00:01:55.630
Oh. my God.

55
00:01:55.630 --> 00:01:57.990
I knew there was someone else.

56
00:01:57.990 --> 00:01:59.870
And it was you!

57
00:01:59.880 --> 00:02:02.040
No. no. it's... it's not.

58
00:02:02.040 --> 00:02:04.240
- (DENISE SCREAMS)
- I mean. not recently.

59
00:02:04.250 --> 00:02:06.550
You're supposed to be my best friend!

60
00:02:06.550 --> 00:02:09.960
(EMILY SCREAMS. GRUNTING)

61
00:02:09.960 --> 00:02:11.000
(SCREAMING)

62
00:02:11.000 --> 00:02:12.460
(BANGING. WHIMPERING)

63
00:02:12.460 --> 00:02:13.440
(EMILY SCREAMING)

64
00:02:15.260 --> 00:02:17.810
(DENISE)

65
00:02:17.810 --> 00:02:20.220
I'm sorry. I can't hear you. What is that noise?
(SCREAMING. BANGING)

66
00:02:20.220 --> 00:02:22.450
<i>(DENISE) My friend! I've unleashed a monster.</i>

67
00:02:22.460 --> 00:02:24.190
<i>- She's gonna kill me.</i>
- Ma'am. can you tell me

68
00:02:24.190 --> 00:02:26.040
- where you're calling from?
<i>- (DENISE) Happy's Rage Room.</i>

69
00:02:26.040 --> 00:02:26.950
<i>downtown!</i>

70
00:02:26.950 --> 00:02:28.580
(HEN) Apart from a blowout bar.

71
00:02:28.590 --> 00:02:31.430
this is the dumbest thing
people in L.A. pay money for.

72
00:02:31.430 --> 00:02:33.380
I think it's genius.

73
00:02:33.380 --> 00:02:35.030
Your victim's in there.

74
00:02:35.030 --> 00:02:36.390
(RADIO CHAT)

75
00:02:36.390 --> 00:02:38.930
- Where?
- (ATHENA SIGHS)

76
00:02:38.930 --> 00:02:41.260
There. Your victim climbed into the barrel

77
00:02:41.270 --> 00:02:43.110
after her BFF started chasing her

78
00:02:43.110 --> 00:02:44.560
- with a sledgehammer.
- I thought the point

79
00:02:44.560 --> 00:02:46.990
was to smash things. not each other.

80
00:02:46.990 --> 00:02:49.290
Wife. Mistress.

81
00:02:49.300 --> 00:02:51.580
Adulterous slut!

82
00:02:51.590 --> 00:02:53.570
Does the adulterous slut have a name?

83
00:02:53.580 --> 00:02:56.160
Denise. She can't hear
you very well in there.

84
00:02:56.160 --> 00:02:58.420
Ears ringing.

85
00:02:58.430 --> 00:03:00.090
(BOBBY) Denise. are you hurt?

86
00:03:00.090 --> 00:03:01.930
- (DENISE) What?
- Ah. looks like

87
00:03:01.930 --> 00:03:04.120
she's sledge hammered in
there pretty good. Cap.

88
00:03:04.120 --> 00:03:05.790
Lena. Eddie. saws and jaws.

89
00:03:05.790 --> 00:03:07.010
On it. Cap.

90
00:03:07.010 --> 00:03:08.620
Denise. we're gonna cut you out of there.

91
00:03:08.630 --> 00:03:10.180
(DENISE) What?

92
00:03:10.180 --> 00:03:11.790
(SAW WHIRRING)

93
00:03:11.800 --> 00:03:14.800
<i>(DRAMATIC MUSIC)</i>

94
00:03:14.800 --> 00:03:21.240
<i>♪ ♪</i>

95
00:03:22.520 --> 00:03:25.490
(METAL GROANING)

96
00:03:29.530 --> 00:03:30.880
You have the right to remain silent.

97
00:03:30.880 --> 00:03:32.940
Wait. excuse me.
Please. don't arrest her.

98
00:03:32.940 --> 00:03:35.020
This is all my fault.

99
00:03:35.030 --> 00:03:37.350
You wanna be a better friend?
Bail her out.

100
00:03:37.350 --> 00:03:39.680
I'd rather rot in jail

101
00:03:39.680 --> 00:03:41.640
than have her do another thing for me.

102
00:03:41.640 --> 00:03:44.220
(EMILY) I should've never trusted you!

103
00:03:44.220 --> 00:03:46.930
Consider this the end of our friendship!

104
00:03:46.930 --> 00:03:48.740
I hate you! Next time...

105
00:03:48.740 --> 00:03:51.550
So much anger in the world these days.

106
00:03:51.550 --> 00:03:53.810
I can see why this place is all the rage.

107
00:03:53.810 --> 00:03:57.320
- See what I did there?
- (SCOFFS) Oh. I see it.

108
00:03:57.320 --> 00:03:59.110
(LAUGHTER)

109
00:03:59.110 --> 00:04:00.820
(INDISTINCT RADIO CHAT)

110
00:04:00.920 --> 00:04:03.940
9-1-1 S03E05
"Rage"

111
00:04:04.040 --> 00:04:06.860
I'm really sorry about this.

112
00:04:06.860 --> 00:04:08.980
I thought I was gonna have the day off.

113
00:04:08.980 --> 00:04:10.480
Oh. it's fine.

114
00:04:10.480 --> 00:04:12.690
Pretty sure I'm gonna have
an easier day than you are.

115
00:04:12.700 --> 00:04:14.620
(CHUCKLES) A root canal would be more fun.

116
00:04:14.620 --> 00:04:16.030
(KAREN CHUCKLES)
(PHONE CHIMES)

117
00:04:16.030 --> 00:04:17.580
(GASPS)

118
00:04:17.580 --> 00:04:19.170
Six...

119
00:04:19.170 --> 00:04:21.490
Six embryos made it.

120
00:04:21.490 --> 00:04:23.490
They're sending them for testing. and then...

121
00:04:23.490 --> 00:04:25.150
(HEN) We can schedule the transfer.

122
00:04:25.150 --> 00:04:27.850
(BOTH LAUGH)

123
00:04:29.540 --> 00:04:30.870
I guess we have to start deciding

124
00:04:30.880 --> 00:04:33.210
exactly how many little pairs of feet

125
00:04:33.210 --> 00:04:35.100
we want stomping around this house.

126
00:04:35.100 --> 00:04:38.190
(BOTH LAUGH)

127
00:04:38.190 --> 00:04:40.110
Mom. have you seen my phone charger?

128
00:04:40.110 --> 00:04:42.010
Why am I the lost and found?

129
00:04:42.010 --> 00:04:46.060
(BAG THUDS)
In the kitchen. Next to the coffee maker.

130
00:04:46.060 --> 00:04:47.590
And Harry! Let's go!

131
00:04:47.590 --> 00:04:48.810
What time are you and Bobby leaving?

132
00:04:48.810 --> 00:04:50.070
We're not.

133
00:04:50.070 --> 00:04:51.230
What? I thought you guys were going

134
00:04:51.230 --> 00:04:53.230
- to that B&B up the coast.
- Canceled.

135
00:04:53.240 --> 00:04:54.430
on account of a lawsuit.

136
00:04:54.430 --> 00:04:56.990
Buck's suing the City to get his job back.

137
00:04:57.000 --> 00:05:00.060
Bobby has to go in for an
arbitration hearing today.

138
00:05:00.060 --> 00:05:02.070
Wow. Last time I saw Buck

139
00:05:02.070 --> 00:05:04.060
he was coughing up blood on the patio.

140
00:05:04.060 --> 00:05:05.910
Oh. yeah. He's a sweet kid.

141
00:05:05.910 --> 00:05:07.910
but I need to stop inviting him over.

142
00:05:07.910 --> 00:05:10.080
Chaos inevitably ensues.

143
00:05:10.080 --> 00:05:11.890
That sounds like a great idea.

144
00:05:11.890 --> 00:05:13.370
None of this would've
happened if you hadn't

145
00:05:13.380 --> 00:05:15.080
invited him over for dinner.

146
00:05:15.090 --> 00:05:16.890
Excuse you.

147
00:05:16.890 --> 00:05:18.560
And that would be my cue.

148
00:05:18.570 --> 00:05:20.890
Hey. Harry! Come on. let's go. man!

149
00:05:20.900 --> 00:05:23.220
You know your grandmother's
expecting us for lunch.

150
00:05:23.220 --> 00:05:25.310
And if we're late. I am definitely blaming you.

151
00:05:25.310 --> 00:05:27.390
It won't matter. It's genetically impossible

152
00:05:27.390 --> 00:05:28.840
for GG to get mad at me.

153
00:05:28.840 --> 00:05:29.880
(LAUGHS)

154
00:05:29.880 --> 00:05:32.340
- Bye. Bobby.
- You two be good.

155
00:05:32.340 --> 00:05:35.230
Don't give your dad too much trouble.

156
00:05:35.230 --> 00:05:38.230
- Give GG a kiss hello for me.
- I will.

157
00:05:38.230 --> 00:05:39.920
Have fun!

158
00:05:41.280 --> 00:05:43.160
(DOOR CLOSES)

159
00:05:43.170 --> 00:05:47.240
So. what is that about this
Buck thing being my fault?

160
00:05:47.240 --> 00:05:50.080
I think I'll exercise my right to remain silent.

161
00:05:50.080 --> 00:05:51.840
I love you.

162
00:05:51.840 --> 00:05:53.430
(LAUGHS)

163
00:05:55.080 --> 00:05:56.380
<i>(ARBITRATOR) This is not a trial.</i>

164
00:05:56.390 --> 00:05:57.840
and I am not a judge.

165
00:05:57.850 --> 00:06:00.460
This arbitration will
address Mr. Buckley's claim

166
00:06:00.470 --> 00:06:02.260
against the Los Angeles Fire Department

167
00:06:02.260 --> 00:06:03.590
for wrongful termination.

168
00:06:03.590 --> 00:06:05.690
Buck wasn't terminated.
He still has his job.

169
00:06:05.690 --> 00:06:07.240
(CHASE) It's our position that Firefighter Buckley.

170
00:06:07.240 --> 00:06:08.760
while not technically fired.

171
00:06:08.760 --> 00:06:10.260
has been constructively terminated

172
00:06:10.270 --> 00:06:12.530
from all components of firefighting duty.

173
00:06:12.530 --> 00:06:14.140
A defacto firing.

174
00:06:14.150 --> 00:06:15.810
Which is a direct result of a pattern

175
00:06:15.810 --> 00:06:17.790
of discriminatory and unequal treatment

176
00:06:17.790 --> 00:06:20.480
- on the part of Captain Nash.
- Unequal treatment?

177
00:06:20.490 --> 00:06:22.440
I don't treat Buck any differently

178
00:06:22.450 --> 00:06:24.790
than I do any other
firefighter under my watch.

179
00:06:24.800 --> 00:06:26.540
- Really?
- Really.

180
00:06:26.540 --> 00:06:29.830
See. I was hit from behind
with a construction truck

181
00:06:29.830 --> 00:06:32.120
and the rebar entered the back of my skull

182
00:06:32.120 --> 00:06:34.550
and went right through my
brain and exited my forehead.

183
00:06:34.550 --> 00:06:37.120
- See that little scar?
- Yeah.

184
00:06:37.130 --> 00:06:39.290
It's all I ended up with.

185
00:06:39.290 --> 00:06:40.650
That's miraculous.

186
00:06:41.860 --> 00:06:44.550
And how long did it take
before you returned to work?

187
00:06:44.560 --> 00:06:46.800
Uh...

188
00:06:46.800 --> 00:06:48.230
several weeks.

189
00:06:48.230 --> 00:06:50.560
No. you know what?
It was more closer to a month.

190
00:06:50.570 --> 00:06:53.020
I'm a quick healer. evidently.

191
00:06:53.020 --> 00:06:54.570
(CHASE) Evidently.

192
00:06:54.570 --> 00:06:57.140
And your more recent medical trauma...

193
00:06:57.150 --> 00:06:58.750
after you were stabbed repeatedly

194
00:06:58.750 --> 00:07:00.330
by your girlfriend's ex-husband...

195
00:07:00.330 --> 00:07:03.240
How long before you
were back with the 118?

196
00:07:03.250 --> 00:07:05.360
That was also about a month.

197
00:07:05.360 --> 00:07:07.190
(CHASE) Hm. So it's fair to say

198
00:07:07.190 --> 00:07:08.440
Captain Nash has followed a pattern

199
00:07:08.440 --> 00:07:10.570
of allowing firefighters
with serious injuries

200
00:07:10.570 --> 00:07:12.470
back after less than a month.

201
00:07:12.480 --> 00:07:15.040
No. I don't think it is fair to say.

202
00:07:15.040 --> 00:07:18.500
Every patient is different.
Every injury is different.

203
00:07:18.500 --> 00:07:20.990
The blood thinners that
Buck has to take right now makes

204
00:07:20.990 --> 00:07:23.250
very dangerous for him to be in the field.

205
00:07:23.260 --> 00:07:25.020
Tell me...

206
00:07:25.030 --> 00:07:26.900
do you recognize this brochure?

207
00:07:29.180 --> 00:07:30.200
Yes.

208
00:07:30.200 --> 00:07:34.370
Can you tell us what it is?

209
00:07:34.370 --> 00:07:37.280
(HEN) It's a commercial
brochure for anticoagulant

210
00:07:37.280 --> 00:07:38.620
blood thinner medication.

211
00:07:38.620 --> 00:07:41.020
Medications that you yourself sold

212
00:07:41.020 --> 00:07:42.770
in your former career
as a pharmaceutical rep.

213
00:07:42.770 --> 00:07:43.900
- Is that right?
- Yes.

214
00:07:43.900 --> 00:07:46.240
And in your sales pitch
to your doctor clients.

215
00:07:46.240 --> 00:07:48.210
was it your contention
that these medications

216
00:07:48.220 --> 00:07:50.600
would allow patients to
resume their normal lives?

217
00:07:50.600 --> 00:07:52.760
I was a sales rep. not a doctor.

218
00:07:52.760 --> 00:07:54.050
But you were a field medic.

219
00:07:54.050 --> 00:07:58.070
Doesn't qualify me to comment
on Buck's medical status.

220
00:07:58.070 --> 00:08:00.370
It does make me understand
the chain of command.

221
00:08:00.380 --> 00:08:02.340
And if Cap says he's not ready. he's not ready.

222
00:08:02.340 --> 00:08:03.970
Were you ready. Firefighter Diaz.

223
00:08:03.970 --> 00:08:05.560
to return to work after your wife's death?

224
00:08:05.570 --> 00:08:06.760
That's my business.

225
00:08:06.760 --> 00:08:08.130
(CHASE) It's also your Captain's business.

226
00:08:08.140 --> 00:08:09.810
He never suggested you take some time?

227
00:08:09.810 --> 00:08:12.310
- See a counselor?
- He wasn't there at the time.

228
00:08:12.460 --> 00:08:13.890
'Cause he'd been suspended.

229
00:08:13.890 --> 00:08:15.890
Captain Nash's suspension was adjudicated.

230
00:08:15.890 --> 00:08:17.410
I don't see how it is relevant

231
00:08:17.420 --> 00:08:18.890
- to this proceeding.
- It's relevant because

232
00:08:18.900 --> 00:08:21.380
it illustrates how everyone except Mr. Buckley

233
00:08:21.380 --> 00:08:22.560
is allowed to return to the job.

234
00:08:22.560 --> 00:08:24.390
no matter the injury or infraction.

235
00:08:24.390 --> 00:08:26.630
Buck has a chronic medical condition.

236
00:08:26.630 --> 00:08:28.400
And what about your own
chronic medical condition.

237
00:08:28.410 --> 00:08:30.070
Captain Nash?

238
00:08:30.070 --> 00:08:31.710
I believe the National Institute of Health

239
00:08:31.710 --> 00:08:35.260
classifies alcoholism as
a chronic brain disease.

240
00:08:35.260 --> 00:08:36.450
I'm clean and sober.

241
00:08:36.450 --> 00:08:38.160
You are now. and you were before.

242
00:08:38.160 --> 00:08:39.760
But isn't it true that just about

243
00:08:39.770 --> 00:08:44.290
a year and a half ago.
you did have a relapse?

244
00:08:44.300 --> 00:08:45.960
I did.

245
00:08:45.960 --> 00:08:48.180
After the Liberty jet crash. I drank.

246
00:08:48.180 --> 00:08:49.380
I was not on duty.

247
00:08:49.380 --> 00:08:50.810
But it was you and Mr. Buckley

248
00:08:50.810 --> 00:08:53.060
who found Bobby passed
out in his apartment.

249
00:08:53.060 --> 00:08:55.690
Yes.

250
00:08:55.690 --> 00:08:57.070
That happened.

251
00:08:59.190 --> 00:09:00.950
I did not know about that.

252
00:09:00.950 --> 00:09:02.980
That was before I got here.

253
00:09:02.980 --> 00:09:05.370
You asked my client for his help that day.

254
00:09:05.370 --> 00:09:07.700
That's exactly what he did. without hesitation.

255
00:09:07.700 --> 00:09:09.870
He helped you get sobered up.

256
00:09:09.870 --> 00:09:12.120
and then you returned to your full duties

257
00:09:12.120 --> 00:09:13.780
as Captain of the 118.

258
00:09:13.780 --> 00:09:16.330
- Yes. that's all true.
- So isn't the only difference

259
00:09:16.340 --> 00:09:18.710
between your off-duty
relapse and Mr. Buckley's

260
00:09:18.710 --> 00:09:20.900
is that he actually did
everything in his power

261
00:09:20.910 --> 00:09:23.240
to help you return to your job.

262
00:09:23.240 --> 00:09:25.240
