320
00:11:40.770 --> 00:11:43.570
I got some bruising. possible
swelling of the trachea.

321
00:11:43.570 --> 00:11:44.820
We're gonna get you to the hospital.

322
00:11:44.830 --> 00:11:45.860
They'll check you out there.

323
00:11:45.860 --> 00:11:48.370
I'm fine. I don't need to go to the hospital.

324
00:11:48.370 --> 00:11:50.460
He needs to go to jail.

325
00:11:50.470 --> 00:11:52.630
(MACHINERY WINDS DOWN)
(DUCKS QUAKING)

326
00:11:52.630 --> 00:11:54.560
Hey. did you just shut that off?

327
00:11:54.560 --> 00:11:56.130
So?

328
00:11:56.140 --> 00:11:58.110
So you could've done
that the whole time.

329
00:11:58.120 --> 00:11:59.100
and you just let it run?

330
00:11:59.100 --> 00:12:00.870
Ah. man. they were trespass...

331
00:12:00.870 --> 00:12:02.540
They're just idiot kids!
They could've died!

332
00:12:02.540 --> 00:12:05.220
Bobby!

333
00:12:05.220 --> 00:12:08.070
(COUGHING)

334
00:12:08.070 --> 00:12:09.600
(GIRL) Toby? Toby?

335
00:12:09.600 --> 00:12:11.630
It's gotta be that key.
Keep coughing. buddy.

336
00:12:11.630 --> 00:12:15.060
- (GIRL) What's happening? What's wrong?
- Starting the Heimlich!

337
00:12:15.060 --> 00:12:16.380
- He's not breathing.
- All right. get him

338
00:12:16.380 --> 00:12:18.250
- on a backboard. now! Let's go!
- (GIRL) Toby?

339
00:12:18.250 --> 00:12:19.550
- Ready?
- (GIRL) What's going on...

340
00:12:20.350 --> 00:12:21.850
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

341
00:12:21.850 --> 00:12:23.590
- (HEN) I got a pulse.
- (CHIMNEY) Let's ventilate.

342
00:12:23.590 --> 00:12:27.070
♪ ♪

343
00:12:27.080 --> 00:12:28.950
He's dying. guys. This is not...

344
00:12:28.950 --> 00:12:30.620
(COUGHING)

345
00:12:30.620 --> 00:12:31.860
The key must've torn his trachea.

346
00:12:31.860 --> 00:12:33.230
We gotta try to get it out.

347
00:12:34.340 --> 00:12:36.630
(CHIMNEY) Lena. my bag. Magill forceps.

348
00:12:36.630 --> 00:12:39.800
Oh. God. Please don't let
him die on my property.

349
00:12:39.800 --> 00:12:42.270
<i>♪ ♪</i>

350
00:12:42.280 --> 00:12:44.680
(RADIO CHAT IN BACKGROUND)

351
00:12:44.690 --> 00:12:47.300
(BLOOD SQUELCHING)
(GIRL) Oh!

352
00:12:48.760 --> 00:12:50.260
(HEN) He's still not breathing.

353
00:12:50.270 --> 00:12:51.620
Two more rescue breaths.

354
00:12:51.620 --> 00:12:53.620
<i>♪ ♪</i>

355
00:12:53.620 --> 00:12:55.620
(AIR PRESSURE HISSING)

356
00:12:55.790 --> 00:12:57.310
Chest is rising.

357
00:12:57.310 --> 00:12:59.200
He's breathing.

358
00:12:59.200 --> 00:13:01.980
You still wanna press charges?

359
00:13:01.990 --> 00:13:03.200
- I think we're good.
- (CHIMNEY) All right.

360
00:13:03.200 --> 00:13:04.790
let's get him on a gurney. on three.

361
00:13:04.800 --> 00:13:06.750
<i> ♪ I'm a sucker for you ♪</i>

362
00:13:06.760 --> 00:13:08.540
<i>♪ ♪</i>

363
00:13:08.540 --> 00:13:10.950
You know. I thought that we agreed

364
00:13:10.950 --> 00:13:13.880
to be technology free on this trip.

365
00:13:13.880 --> 00:13:17.460
We just passed L.A. city limit.

366
00:13:17.460 --> 00:13:19.670
- Oh. God.
- (MICHAEL LAUGHS)

367
00:13:19.670 --> 00:13:21.150
Could you at least check on your brother

368
00:13:21.150 --> 00:13:22.740
and make sure he's still breathing.

369
00:13:22.740 --> 00:13:24.800
I think he's in a food
coma from GG's cooking.

370
00:13:24.800 --> 00:13:27.010
Ohh. that's the only way to go.

371
00:13:27.010 --> 00:13:29.320
(BOTH LAUGH)

372
00:13:29.320 --> 00:13:30.990
Ooh!

373
00:13:32.490 --> 00:13:35.640
Mm. call your mother and
tell her we'll be home

374
00:13:35.640 --> 00:13:38.190
- in about half an hour.
- Okay.

375
00:13:38.190 --> 00:13:41.670
(SIREN CHIRPS. HORN BLARES)

376
00:13:41.670 --> 00:13:44.710
Or not.
(SIREN CONTINUES)

377
00:13:53.330 --> 00:13:54.640
Come on!

378
00:13:54.640 --> 00:13:56.640
(SIREN WHOOPS)

379
00:14:00.020 --> 00:14:03.100
<i>(RADIO CHATTER)</i>

380
00:14:03.100 --> 00:14:09.740
<i>♪ ♪</i>

381
00:14:09.740 --> 00:14:11.280
Hey.

382
00:14:12.270 --> 00:14:15.370
License and registration.

383
00:14:15.370 --> 00:14:18.290
It's in the glove box.
You mind if I reach for it?

384
00:14:20.060 --> 00:14:21.450
All right.

385
00:14:21.450 --> 00:14:23.780
(OPENS GLOVE BOX)

386
00:14:23.790 --> 00:14:25.790
All right. Here you go.

387
00:14:25.790 --> 00:14:27.790
This your car?

388
00:14:27.790 --> 00:14:30.290
It's on the paperwork.

389
00:14:30.290 --> 00:14:32.030
Step out of the car. sir.

390
00:14:32.030 --> 00:14:34.740
What? Why?

391
00:14:34.750 --> 00:14:36.700
Ah. it's fine. baby.

392
00:14:36.710 --> 00:14:38.430
Sit tight.

393
00:14:43.250 --> 00:14:44.380
Where you coming from?

394
00:14:44.380 --> 00:14:46.640
Visiting my mother.

395
00:14:46.640 --> 00:14:48.680
Do you mind if I ask
why you pulled me over?

396
00:14:48.680 --> 00:14:50.900
Expired tags.

397
00:14:50.900 --> 00:14:52.590
Wait here while I run your information.

398
00:14:52.600 --> 00:14:54.600
Oh. wait a minute. Wait. I... I actually

399
00:14:54.600 --> 00:14:55.980
- have the tags in my car...
- Don't move.

400
00:14:55.980 --> 00:14:58.240
Turn around. put your hands on the hood

401
00:14:58.240 --> 00:14:59.770
and wait here while I run your plates.

402
00:14:59.770 --> 00:15:01.820
Excuse me? Hold on for a second.

403
00:15:01.820 --> 00:15:04.250
- I said don't move!
- Oh! Okay. okay. okay!

404
00:15:04.250 --> 00:15:05.490
Hands on the hood!
(PHONE BEEPS)

405
00:15:05.490 --> 00:15:06.730
(OFFICER) Our friend here is having trouble

406
00:15:06.740 --> 00:15:08.280
listening to directions.

407
00:15:08.280 --> 00:15:09.880
- Please. miss.
- What are you doing to my dad?

408
00:15:09.880 --> 00:15:12.380
- Get back in the vehicle.
- May. get back in the car!

409
00:15:12.380 --> 00:15:13.760
- Do what he says.
- No. they can't just

410
00:15:13.760 --> 00:15:15.760
- treat us like this.
- (OFFICER) Take her phone.

411
00:15:15.760 --> 00:15:17.260
- Stop.
- Back seat!

412
00:15:17.260 --> 00:15:18.640
- No. no. no!
- Dad!

413
00:15:18.640 --> 00:15:19.600
- Hands in the air!
- No. no. stop. stop. stop!

414
00:15:19.600 --> 00:15:21.190
- No!
- Hands in the...

415
00:15:21.190 --> 00:15:22.360
- Get off me!
- (ALL SHOUTING)

416
00:15:22.360 --> 00:15:24.120
- Back in the car. now!
- Do not move!

417
00:15:24.120 --> 00:15:27.210
Please don't shoot my son!
Don't you shoot my son!

418
00:15:28.700 --> 00:15:31.700
Look. my wife is a sergeant.

419
00:15:31.700 --> 00:15:35.820
Her name is Athena Grant. LAPD.

420
00:15:35.820 --> 00:15:37.130
Please.

421
00:15:37.130 --> 00:15:40.300
<i>♪ ♪</i>

422
00:15:40.300 --> 00:15:42.300
(RADIO CHAT)

423
00:15:43.000 --> 00:15:45.970
<i>(SOMBER MUSIC)</i>

424
00:15:45.980 --> 00:15:47.980
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

425
00:15:47.980 --> 00:15:51.630
♪♪

426
00:15:51.630 --> 00:15:53.230
It's just a kid.

427
00:15:55.300 --> 00:15:58.740
Come here. Come here.
come here. come here.

428
00:15:59.880 --> 00:16:02.900
Okay. It's okay. Harry. sit tight. man.

429
00:16:02.900 --> 00:16:04.850
It's all good. We got this.

430
00:16:04.850 --> 00:16:06.080
- Yeah.
- C'mon.

431
00:16:10.000 --> 00:16:11.740
You folks have a nice night. then.

432
00:16:11.740 --> 00:16:18.670
<i>♪ ♪</i>

433
00:16:20.200 --> 00:16:21.920
Come on.

434
00:16:21.920 --> 00:16:26.330
Come here. man. Ahh.

435
00:16:26.330 --> 00:16:28.920
Ahh. okay. We're good.
(CAR DOOR OPENS)

436
00:16:28.930 --> 00:16:30.830
(MICHAEL) We're good.
You get in the car. now.

437
00:16:30.840 --> 00:16:34.100
Let's go. Let's go. yeah? All right.

438
00:16:34.100 --> 00:16:38.100
<i>♪ ♪</i>

439
00:16:39.800 --> 00:16:42.800
(SEAT BELTS CLICK)

440
00:16:43.530 --> 00:16:46.180
(ENGINE STARTS. SIREN CHIRPS)

441
00:16:46.190 --> 00:16:49.580
<i>♪ ♪</i>

442
00:16:56.670 --> 00:16:59.580
Shoot first. and then ask questions later.

443
00:16:59.580 --> 00:17:00.740
That's how they're trained.

444
00:17:00.740 --> 00:17:03.200
But they didn't fire
their weapons. thank God.

445
00:17:03.200 --> 00:17:06.120
All right? It was just
a bad stop. They happen.

446
00:17:06.130 --> 00:17:08.410
They pulled their guns. Athena.

447
00:17:08.420 --> 00:17:10.560
It wasn't just a bad stop.

448
00:17:10.560 --> 00:17:13.860
We will file a complaint.
There will be an investigation.

449
00:17:13.860 --> 00:17:15.320
And what do you think the determination

450
00:17:15.320 --> 00:17:16.530
will be of that?

451
00:17:16.530 --> 00:17:18.030
Let me save you the paperwork.

452
00:17:18.030 --> 00:17:21.700
We'd be lucky for a slap on the wrist.

453
00:17:21.700 --> 00:17:23.300
Is Dad gonna get arrested?

454
00:17:23.300 --> 00:17:26.390
What? No. man. Come here.

455
00:17:26.390 --> 00:17:28.080
Hey. listen. my man.

456
00:17:28.090 --> 00:17:30.250
Daddy's not going anywhere. It's okay.

457
00:17:30.250 --> 00:17:32.050
No. it's not okay.

458
00:17:32.050 --> 00:17:33.810
They could've killed Harry.
and they could've killed you.

459
00:17:33.810 --> 00:17:35.400
May. Please. now.

460
00:17:35.400 --> 00:17:38.140
What? It's the truth.

461
00:17:38.150 --> 00:17:39.460
Why do they do that to us?

462
00:17:39.460 --> 00:17:43.150
'Cause they were afraid. honey.
And they overreacted.

463
00:17:43.150 --> 00:17:45.580
They were afraid because they saw me

464
00:17:45.580 --> 00:17:48.330
as a big. scary black man.

465
00:17:48.340 --> 00:17:49.900
Well. arguing with the police

466
00:17:49.900 --> 00:17:51.600
probably wasn't the best choice.

467
00:17:51.600 --> 00:17:53.390
Wait a minute. Are you blaming me for this?

468
00:17:53.390 --> 00:17:54.590
No.

469
00:17:54.590 --> 00:17:56.780
Well. you're giving them
the benefit of the doubt.

470
00:17:56.780 --> 00:17:58.610
- Because I am them!
- Right.

471
00:17:58.610 --> 00:18:00.170
All right. I know what it's like.

472
00:18:00.170 --> 00:18:02.120
You're walking up to a car. all right?

473
00:18:02.120 --> 00:18:03.840
You're out in the open. exposed.

474
00:18:03.840 --> 00:18:05.410
You don't know what's waiting for you

475
00:18:05.410 --> 00:18:07.140
when you walk up to that window.

476
00:18:07.140 --> 00:18:09.840
It's a father and his two kids.

477
00:18:09.840 --> 00:18:12.290
So you don't think that
maybe that was the moment

478
00:18:12.300 --> 00:18:15.940
- that they should've stood down?
- Yes! All right?

479
00:18:15.940 --> 00:18:19.280
And the idea of what could've
happened terrifies me.

480
00:18:19.280 --> 00:18:23.170
So it's not as simple as pick a side.

481
00:18:23.170 --> 00:18:26.040
How can you be a cop when they
treat black people like this?

482
00:18:26.050 --> 00:18:28.440
It is not all cops. May.

483
00:18:28.440 --> 00:18:30.270
The good outnumber the bad.

484
00:18:30.270 --> 00:18:32.030
Not when the good choose
to look the other way

485
00:18:32.030 --> 00:18:33.190
when the bad do stuff like this.

486
00:18:33.190 --> 00:18:35.160
No one is looking the other way.

487
00:18:35.160 --> 00:18:38.040
Really? Because those
cops will go home tonight

488
00:18:38.040 --> 00:18:39.740
and they'll probably sleep easy.

489
00:18:39.750 --> 00:18:41.670
Business as usual for them.

490
00:18:41.680 --> 00:18:44.970
But our son and daughter are
sitting here. traumatized.

491
00:18:44.970 --> 00:18:46.300
You know what?

492
00:18:46.310 --> 00:18:47.990
They're not gonna forget
what they did to us. okay?

493
00:18:47.990 --> 00:18:50.150
I have it all on my cell phone.
I'm posting the video.

494
00:18:50.150 --> 00:18:51.480
You will not.

495
00:18:51.480 --> 00:18:53.740
We do not need that kind of attention.

496
00:18:53.750 --> 00:18:55.150
This family doesn't.

497
00:18:55.150 --> 00:18:57.160
You and Harry's face online.

498
00:18:57.170 --> 00:18:59.910
just forever associated with that incident.

499
00:18:59.910 --> 00:19:01.880
I do not want that for you.

500
00:19:03.120 --> 00:19:05.220
You're right. you're right. you're right.

501
00:19:05.220 --> 00:19:06.440
Your mother... Your mother's right.

502
00:19:06.450 --> 00:19:08.450
Besides. nobody got shot. right?

503
00:19:08.450 --> 00:19:11.400
Probably wouldn't get that
much of a reaction anyway.

504
00:19:11.400 --> 00:19:14.090
Michael. the police are not the enemy.

505
00:19:14.090 --> 00:19:16.850
All right? It's not us versus them.

506
00:19:16.850 --> 00:19:19.280
I do not wanna teach our kids that.

507
00:19:19.280 --> 00:19:21.710
Then tell your colleagues that.

508
00:19:21.720 --> 00:19:23.010
Because that's how I felt

509
00:19:23.010 --> 00:19:25.480
when they pulled a gun out on our son!

510
00:19:28.030 --> 00:19:29.910
(SIGHS)

511
00:19:31.890 --> 00:19:33.890
(SIGHS SHARPLY)

512
00:19:33.890 --> 00:19:35.110
Okay. bud.

513
00:19:35.110 --> 00:19:38.560
Let's go. (GRUNTS IN STRENGTH)

514
00:19:38.570 --> 00:19:40.710
All right. strong legs. There we go.

515
00:19:40.710 --> 00:19:42.620
Are you sure about this?

516
00:19:42.620 --> 00:19:44.470
I'm gonna have Carla pick
you up after the party.

517
00:19:44.470 --> 00:19:46.960
No. Dad. I... I wanna go.

518
00:19:46.960 --> 00:19:49.220
Hey. guys! You made it!

519
00:19:49.370 --> 00:19:51.190
Dillon is so excited!

520
00:19:51.190 --> 00:19:52.920
Maybe now he'll stop talking about it.

521
00:19:52.930 --> 00:19:54.730
Wait. who am I kidding? No. he won't.

522
00:19:54.730 --> 00:19:56.260
- (WOMAN LAUGHS)
- You got my emails. right?

523
00:19:56.260 --> 00:19:59.230
I did. Very detailed.

524
00:19:59.240 --> 00:20:01.530
All right. Be good. have fun.

525
00:20:01.530 --> 00:20:03.240
Call me if you need anything. okay?

526
00:20:03.240 --> 00:20:05.220
Okay. Dad. I love you.

527
00:20:05.220 --> 00:20:07.910
I love you too. kid.

528
00:20:07.910 --> 00:20:10.220
All right. Go. go. go. go. go. go. go.

529
00:20:10.220 --> 00:20:13.310
(LAUGHING)

530
00:20:14.800 --> 00:20:16.920
- Thank you.
- Mm-hmm.

531
00:20:16.920 --> 00:20:19.560
He's going to be okay. Eddie.

532
00:20:19.570 --> 00:20:22.400
(EDDIE) I know.
He hasn't had a nightmare in a week.

533
00:20:22.400 --> 00:20:25.140
The doctor says a sleepover
will be great for him.

534
00:20:25.150 --> 00:20:27.150
I'm not sure how good it's gonna be for me.

535
00:20:27.150 --> 00:20:28.590
Listen. don't worry.

536
00:20:28.590 --> 00:20:30.610
Dillon's got this
whole camping situation

537
00:20:30.610 --> 00:20:31.570
set up in the backyard.

538
00:20:31.570 --> 00:20:33.490
and Ron'll be in the tent next to them.

539
00:20:33.490 --> 00:20:35.270
Okay. we'll call you if there's any problem.

540
00:20:35.270 --> 00:20:37.580
Now. go relax. Recharge.

541
00:20:37.580 --> 00:20:41.250
I will return him to you in one piece tomorrow.

542
00:20:41.250 --> 00:20:43.750
- Thanks. Tasha.
- Mm-hmm.

543
00:20:45.050 --> 00:20:47.750
(CHILDREN SHOUT PLAYINGFULLY IN DISTANCE)

544
00:20:51.630 --> 00:20:53.780
Hey. that's a handicapped spot.

545
00:20:53.780 --> 00:20:55.280
- I know.
- Oh. you know.

546
00:20:55.280 --> 00:20:56.870
(LAUGHS) Oh. that's rich.

547
00:20:56.880 --> 00:20:58.950
I had knee surgery and
had to park three rows in. but.

548
00:20:58.950 --> 00:21:00.790
uh. look at you.

549
00:21:00.790 --> 00:21:02.460
Must be nice to own the world.

550
00:21:02.460 --> 00:21:04.000
Look. I'm not doing this with you. man.

551
00:21:04.000 --> 00:21:06.640
My kid has CP. and I just dropped him off.

552
00:21:06.650 --> 00:21:08.000
Yeah. I'm sure. Like those guys

553
00:21:08.000 --> 00:21:09.960
that put dummies in their passenger seats

554
00:21:09.970 --> 00:21:13.000
so they can use the carpool lane.

555
00:21:13.010 --> 00:21:15.490
- Did you just insult my kid?
- I ain't insulting anybody.

556
00:21:15.490 --> 00:21:16.750
I'm calling you out.

557
00:21:16.750 --> 00:21:18.340
You got something to say about that?

558
00:21:18.340 --> 00:21:19.670
(SIREN WAILS)

559
00:21:19.680 --> 00:21:20.680
(GATE BUZZING)

560
00:21:20.680 --> 00:21:22.180
Thanks for coming to bail me out.

561
00:21:22.190 --> 00:21:23.750
I was surprised to get your call.

562
00:21:23.750 --> 00:21:24.810
I didn't realize we reached

563
00:21:24.820 --> 00:21:26.830
the bail each other out of
jail phase of our friendship.

564
00:21:26.830 --> 00:21:28.590
(EDDIE) Well. there's no way
I was gonna call my abuela

565
00:21:28.590 --> 00:21:31.540
or the 118. and I'm not
allowed to talk to Buck.

566
00:21:31.550 --> 00:21:32.980
Look. I don't mind the bailing.

567
00:21:32.980 --> 00:21:35.040
but I'm a little concerned about the jailing part.

568
00:21:35.040 --> 00:21:36.670
I guess I just snapped.

569
00:21:36.680 --> 00:21:39.100
- You punched a handicapped guy.
- He wasn't handicapped.

570
00:21:39.100 --> 00:21:40.990
He had a bad... he had a bad knee.

571
00:21:40.990 --> 00:21:41.940
there's a difference.

572
00:21:41.940 --> 00:21:43.390
It won't happen again.

573
00:21:43.390 --> 00:21:45.220
- Lesson learned.
- Hope so.

574
00:21:45.230 --> 00:21:48.350
I also hope this guy
doesn't have a lawyer.

575
00:21:48.350 --> 00:21:51.520
<i>♪ ♪</i>

576
00:21:51.520 --> 00:21:53.360
(KNOCKING)

577
00:21:53.360 --> 00:21:56.360
Yeah. I got a client meeting.
I'll call you back.

578
00:21:56.360 --> 00:21:58.290
Boy. you got here fast.

579
00:21:58.290 --> 00:22:00.380
Hope you didn't break
any laws on the way here.

580
00:22:00.380 --> 00:22:01.710
Though. I do know someone.

581
00:22:01.710 --> 00:22:05.280
You. uh. you said you had big news?

582
00:22:05.290 --> 00:22:06.550
The biggest.

583
00:22:08.920 --> 00:22:12.310
- Uh. what... what is this?
- That is the City's offer.

584
00:22:12.320 --> 00:22:15.060
They wanna settle.
Now. it's only a jumping off point.

585
00:22:15.060 --> 00:22:16.400
We can counter.

586
00:22:16.400 --> 00:22:18.730
Th... This is all they're offering?

587
00:22:18.730 --> 00:22:23.150
(LAUGHS) Did I. uh... Did I forget a zero?

588
00:22:23.150 --> 00:22:24.220
No. I got it right.

589
00:22:24.220 --> 00:22:25.710
You do understand they're offering you

590
00:22:25.710 --> 00:22:27.740
- millions of dollars.
- I don't want millions.

591
00:22:27.740 --> 00:22:28.930
I... I want my job back.

592
00:22:28.930 --> 00:22:30.620
That was the whole
point in us doing this.

593
00:22:30.620 --> 00:22:32.990
But you'd be a millionaire.
Congratulations.

594
00:22:32.990 --> 00:22:34.400
You never have to have a job again.

595
00:22:34.400 --> 00:22:36.810
Yeah. I didn't do this for money.

596
00:22:36.820 --> 00:22:40.440
I did this so that I could
go back to doing what I love.

597
00:22:40.450 --> 00:22:42.570
To be back with my team.

598
00:22:42.570 --> 00:22:45.760
(CHUCKLES)

599
00:22:45.760 --> 00:22:49.840
Uh. you really think they're
gonna welcome you back. kid?

600
00:22:49.840 --> 00:22:51.410
I mean. not to toot my own horn.

601
00:22:51.410 --> 00:22:54.460
but I raked your friends
over the coals pretty hard.

602
00:22:54.460 --> 00:22:57.350
Wait. I told you that stuff.
not so that you would use it.

603
00:22:57.350 --> 00:22:58.770
it was just information.

604
00:22:58.780 --> 00:23:01.110
What happened to
attorney-client privilege?

605
00:23:01.110 --> 00:23:02.740
Okay. that doesn't work
how you think it does.

606
00:23:02.740 --> 00:23:06.950
But I did exactly what you asked me to do.

607
00:23:06.950 --> 00:23:09.430
We won. Maybe not how you wanted. but...

608
00:23:09.430 --> 00:23:11.770
Well. this doesn't feel like winning.

609
00:23:11.770 --> 00:23:14.330
But it's probably as close
as you're ever gonna get.

610
00:23:16.150 --> 00:23:18.330
So what do you wanna do?

611
00:23:26.040 --> 00:23:27.060
<i>(MAY) What are you doing to my dad?</i>

612
00:23:27.060 --> 00:23:28.500
<i>(YOUNG OFFICER) Miss. get back in the vehicle.</i>

613
00:23:28.500 --> 00:23:30.230
<i>(MICHAEL) May. get back in the car.</i>

614
00:23:30.230 --> 00:23:31.690
<i>Okay. do what he says.</i>

615
00:23:31.690 --> 00:23:33.180
<i>(MAY) No. they can't
just treat us like this.</i>

616
00:23:33.180 --> 00:23:35.450
<i>- (OLD OFFICER) Take her phone.
- MAY: No.</i>

617
00:23:35.460 --> 00:23:37.480
<i>- (YOUNG OFFICER) Back seat.
- (MAY) No. no. stop!</i>

618
00:23:37.480 --> 00:23:38.550
<i>(YOUNG OFFICER) Hands in the air!</i>

619
00:23:38.560 --> 00:23:39.480
<i>(SHOUTING. STRUGGLING EFFORTS)</i>

620
00:23:39.480 --> 00:23:40.660
<i>(MAY) Stop! Stop!</i>

621
00:23:40.660 --> 00:23:42.340
<i>(YOUNG OFFICER) Get back in the car. now!</i>

622
00:23:42.340 --> 00:23:43.390
<i>- (MAY) Leave us alone!
- (MICHAEL) Don't shoot my son!</i>

623
00:23:43.390 --> 00:23:44.950
<i>Don't you shoot my son!</i>

624
00:23:44.950 --> 00:23:49.060
<i>Look. my wife is a sergeant.
Her name is Athena Grant.</i>

625
00:23:49.070 --> 00:23:50.680
You sure you wanna watch that?

626
00:23:50.680 --> 00:23:53.900
I needed to see it for myself.

627
00:23:53.900 --> 00:23:56.410
I'm gonna recommend
suspension without pay

628
00:23:56.410 --> 00:23:58.740
while the department
conducts their investigation.

629
00:23:58.740 --> 00:24:01.670
I'm gonna push for disciplinary action. but...

630
00:24:01.670 --> 00:24:02.910
Most likely. there'll be

631
00:24:02.910 --> 00:24:04.750
no real consequences for their actions?

632
00:24:04.750 --> 00:24:06.840
None that will feel satisfying.

633
00:24:06.840 --> 00:24:09.800
Reynolds has a long list of complaints.

634
00:24:11.330 --> 00:24:14.990
Excessive force. unlawful
search and seizure.

635
00:24:14.990 --> 00:24:16.700
violation of civil liberties.

636
00:24:16.700 --> 00:24:19.040
Yeah. the problem is he
always stops just short

637
00:24:19.050 --> 00:24:21.410
of doing something truly
awful. so none of it sticks.

638
00:24:21.410 --> 00:24:23.010
Well. maybe it has something to do

639
00:24:23.010 --> 00:24:25.100
with who's making the complaints.
(TELEPHONE RINGS)

640
00:24:25.100 --> 00:24:26.940
Almost every incident on that list
(TELEPHONE RINGS)

641
00:24:26.940 --> 00:24:29.270
involves a black or brown suspect.

642
00:24:29.270 --> 00:24:31.870
I'm aware of the pattern.

643
00:24:31.870 --> 00:24:33.390
But I'm not gonna lie to you. Athena.

644
00:24:33.390 --> 00:24:36.060
This is probably gonna go away. too.

645
00:24:36.060 --> 00:24:39.370
Yeah. for them. But not for my family.

646
00:24:39.380 --> 00:24:41.290
Certainly not for me.

647
00:24:46.360 --> 00:24:48.070
(SHOUTING. CLAMORING)

648
00:24:48.070 --> 00:24:51.080
<i>(ROCK MUSIC)</i>

649
00:24:51.080 --> 00:24:53.050
<i>♪ ♪</i>

650
00:24:53.060 --> 00:24:54.890
(GRUNTING)

651
00:24:54.890 --> 00:24:58.880
<i>♪ ♪</i>

652
00:24:58.880 --> 00:25:02.420
(FIGHTING GRUNTS)
(PEOPLE CHEERING)

653
00:25:02.420 --> 00:25:08.720
<i>♪ ♪</i>

654
00:25:08.720 --> 00:25:09.930
Stock market's closed

655
00:25:09.930 --> 00:25:12.090
you don't need to check your portfolio.

656
00:25:12.090 --> 00:25:13.970
I'm making sure Christopher didn't text.

657
00:25:13.980 --> 00:25:15.210
He's not gonna text.

658
00:25:15.220 --> 00:25:16.740
He's having the time of his life.

659
00:25:16.740 --> 00:25:17.750
You. on the other hand.

660
00:25:17.750 --> 00:25:19.260
are so amped you can't see straight.

661
00:25:19.260 --> 00:25:21.940
What am I missing. anyways.
besides fake fight club.

662
00:25:21.940 --> 00:25:23.920
This is your idea of helping me.

663
00:25:23.920 --> 00:25:25.010
You're a powder keg.

664
00:25:25.010 --> 00:25:27.550
You beat up a guy over a parking space.

665
00:25:27.550 --> 00:25:28.920
But a place like this could be

666
00:25:28.920 --> 00:25:30.500
a healthy outlet for your issues.

667
00:25:30.500 --> 00:25:32.740
(LAUGHS)

668
00:25:32.740 --> 00:25:34.290
What are you. my therapist now?

669
00:25:34.290 --> 00:25:36.760
Just the chick who bailed you out of jail.

670
00:25:36.770 --> 00:25:38.760
I thought we weren't talking about that.
(PEOPLE APPLAUDING)

671
00:25:38.760 --> 00:25:40.760
(FIGHT ORGANIZER) Bosko! You're up!

672
00:25:43.130 --> 00:25:45.460
(LAUGHS) Wait. wait. You're fighting.

673
00:25:45.470 --> 00:25:47.760
I'm not the only one with stuff to work out.

674
00:25:47.760 --> 00:25:49.430
Hold my beer.

675
00:25:49.430 --> 00:25:51.800
<i>♪ BIKINI KILL'S ♪
♪ "REBEL GIRL" PLAYS ♪ </i>

676
00:25:51.810 --> 00:25:53.450
<i>♪ That girl thinks she's the queen ♪</i>

677
00:25:53.450 --> 00:25:55.310
<i>♪ Of the neighborhood ♪</i>

678
00:25:55.310 --> 00:25:57.690
<i>♪ She's got the hottest trike in town ♪</i>

679
00:25:57.690 --> 00:25:59.190
(CHEERING)

680
00:25:59.200 --> 00:26:01.960
<i>♪ That girl. she holds her head up so high ♪</i>

681
00:26:01.960 --> 00:26:05.630
<i>♪ I think I wanna be her best friend. yeah ♪</i>

682
00:26:05.630 --> 00:26:08.270
<i>♪ Rebel girl. rebel girl ♪</i>

683
00:26:08.470 --> 00:26:11.820
(GRUNTS)

684
00:26:11.830 --> 00:26:15.640
(GRUNTING. CHEERING)

685
00:26:15.640 --> 00:26:19.460
(CROWD CLAMORING)

686
00:26:19.460 --> 00:26:21.620
(GRUNTS)

687
00:26:21.630 --> 00:26:23.390
(BOTH GRUNT)

688
00:26:23.390 --> 00:26:24.520
(MAN) Whoa!

689
00:26:25.980 --> 00:26:29.070
(FIGHTERS GRUNTING)

690
00:26:32.060 --> 00:26:34.950
(CHEERING)

691
00:26:36.950 --> 00:26:39.950
(PEOPLE CHANTING)

692
00:26:39.950 --> 00:26:41.950
(SOUND FADES OUT)

693
00:26:41.950 --> 00:26:43.950
(DOG BARKS DISTANTLY)

694
00:26:43.950 --> 00:26:45.950
(CRICKETS CHIRPING)

695
00:26:47.740 --> 00:26:49.910
(MICHAEL) Thanks for dinner. Bobby.

696
00:26:49.910 --> 00:26:52.860
I really needed to see my kids. you know?

697
00:26:52.870 --> 00:26:54.030
How are you doing?

698
00:26:54.030 --> 00:26:56.810
Ah. I'm still mad as hell.

699
00:26:56.820 --> 00:27:00.600
Me too. I thought the world had changed.

700
00:27:00.610 --> 00:27:02.850
Or I guess I wanted to believe it had.

701
00:27:02.850 --> 00:27:06.170
No. it's not just you.

702
00:27:06.170 --> 00:27:08.430
I got too comfortable. You know.

703
00:27:08.430 --> 00:27:10.790
architect. nice house. nice car.

704
00:27:10.800 --> 00:27:13.270
married to an LAPD sergeant.

705
00:27:13.270 --> 00:27:16.030
(CHUCKLES)

706
00:27:16.030 --> 00:27:18.350
Formerly married.

707
00:27:18.350 --> 00:27:20.250
I thought I was exempt.

708
00:27:20.250 --> 00:27:24.040
And then I was reminded that I'm not.

709
00:27:24.040 --> 00:27:27.400
And neither is my son.

710
00:27:27.400 --> 00:27:30.630
And that's the part that
I'm really struggling with.

711
00:27:30.630 --> 00:27:32.590
Because that's the promise
that we make. right?

712
00:27:32.590 --> 00:27:34.140
When we have kids...

713
00:27:34.140 --> 00:27:35.580
that their lives are gonna be

714
00:27:35.580 --> 00:27:37.550
better and easier than ours were.

715
00:27:37.550 --> 00:27:40.910
Yeah. but Harry's ten.

716
00:27:40.910 --> 00:27:42.540
He shouldn't be worried about anything.

717
00:27:42.540 --> 00:27:44.990
except for school. sports
and just being a kid.

718
00:27:44.990 --> 00:27:48.920
And now I have to sit
him down and talk to him.

719
00:27:48.920 --> 00:27:51.900
The talk.

720
00:27:51.900 --> 00:27:53.640
I have to prepare my son for something

721
00:27:53.640 --> 00:27:56.070
that shouldn't even be his responsibility.

722
00:27:56.070 --> 00:27:58.070
I'm sorry. I wish I could say

723
00:27:58.080 --> 00:27:59.220
that I know what you're feeling.

724
00:27:59.230 --> 00:28:02.890
No. brother. I'm so glad that you don't.

725
00:28:02.890 --> 00:28:04.410
If it had been worse.

726
00:28:04.420 --> 00:28:06.010
if something would've happened to me.

727
00:28:06.010 --> 00:28:08.420
I am so happy that they have you

728
00:28:08.420 --> 00:28:12.340
because I know you love
them like they're your own.

729
00:28:12.340 --> 00:28:14.560
No. Michael.
You can't let yourself think like that.

730
00:28:14.560 --> 00:28:16.410
Yeah.

731
00:28:16.410 --> 00:28:19.780
Somehow. I can't seem to stop.

732
00:28:19.790 --> 00:28:22.600
<i>(SOMBER MUSIC)</i>

733
00:28:22.600 --> 00:28:23.930
<i>♪ ♪</i>

734
00:28:23.930 --> 00:28:25.290
<i>(MICHAEL) I need to talk to you</i>

735
00:28:25.290 --> 00:28:27.410
about what happened the other night.

736
00:28:27.410 --> 00:28:30.910
Do we have to?

737
00:28:30.920 --> 00:28:33.990
I know it was scary.

738
00:28:34.000 --> 00:28:35.550
But we need to talk about

739
00:28:35.550 --> 00:28:37.590
what I could've done differently.

740
00:28:37.590 --> 00:28:39.110
You didn't do anything wrong.

741
00:28:39.110 --> 00:28:42.130
Well. it's not about being right.

742
00:28:42.130 --> 00:28:44.690
Sometimes when you deal with the police.

743
00:28:44.700 --> 00:28:46.790
it's about being safe.

744
00:28:46.790 --> 00:28:48.620
Aren't they supposed to keep us safe?

745
00:28:48.620 --> 00:28:50.630
They are.

746
00:28:50.640 --> 00:28:54.370
But not all officers are like your mom.

747
00:28:54.370 --> 00:28:57.300
There are some bad ones.

748
00:28:57.300 --> 00:29:01.160
And there are some that aren't so bad.

749
00:29:01.160 --> 00:29:03.530
But some of them will still treat you

750
00:29:03.540 --> 00:29:06.220
like you're different than the other kids.

751
00:29:06.220 --> 00:29:09.320
Because I'm black?

752
00:29:09.320 --> 00:29:12.070
Yes. because you're black.

753
00:29:14.560 --> 00:29:17.880
So you need to know what to do

754
00:29:17.880 --> 00:29:21.060
when you come in contact with the police.

755
00:29:21.060 --> 00:29:23.490
Be respectful.

756
00:29:23.490 --> 00:29:27.020
Do what they say.

757
00:29:27.020 --> 00:29:31.860
And don't ever make them
feel nervous or panic.

758
00:29:31.860 --> 00:29:33.690
But they're the ones with the guns.

759
00:29:33.700 --> 00:29:35.340
What if I'm more scared than they are?

760
00:29:35.340 --> 00:29:37.720
You probably will be.

761
00:29:37.730 --> 00:29:40.250
But they might not understand that.

762
00:29:40.250 --> 00:29:43.230
So you can't yell or argue with them.

763
00:29:43.240 --> 00:29:45.690
even though you think that you're right.

764
00:29:45.690 --> 00:29:50.520
And always keep your hands
where they can see them.

765
00:29:50.520 --> 00:29:54.880
No sudden moves.
Don't reach for anything. Ever.

766
00:29:54.880 --> 00:29:56.510
What if they ask me for something?

767
00:29:56.510 --> 00:29:58.000
I don't have a driver's license. but...

768
00:29:58.000 --> 00:30:01.560
Right. Well. then you
ask them for permission.

769
00:30:01.560 --> 00:30:03.320
Okay?

770
00:30:03.330 --> 00:30:05.780
And then you move very slowly

771
00:30:05.780 --> 00:30:08.240
and you tell them what you're doing

772
00:30:08.240 --> 00:30:09.730
as you're doing it.

773
00:30:09.730 --> 00:30:12.150
Why are we different?

774
00:30:12.160 --> 00:30:13.540
We are not.

775
00:30:13.540 --> 00:30:15.390
But you just said...

776
00:30:15.390 --> 00:30:19.710
I said that some people will see you differently.

777
00:30:19.720 --> 00:30:22.740
They will look at you and judge you.

778
00:30:22.740 --> 00:30:27.090
But those people will
never know who you are.

779
00:30:27.100 --> 00:30:32.250
You are a smart. kind.

780
00:30:32.250 --> 00:30:36.100
beautiful black boy

781
00:30:36.100 --> 00:30:41.420
who's gonna grow up to
be an amazing black man.

782
00:30:42.680 --> 00:30:44.630
Be proud of that.

783
00:30:44.630 --> 00:30:48.260
Don't you ever forget. Promise me.

784
00:30:48.270 --> 00:30:50.430
I promise.

785
00:30:50.440 --> 00:30:52.160
Good.

786
00:30:52.160 --> 00:30:53.750
I love you. Harry.

787
00:30:53.750 --> 00:30:55.900
I love you too. Dad.

788
00:30:55.900 --> 00:31:02.760
<i>♪ ♪</i>

789
00:31:09.670 --> 00:31:12.600
(SIREN CHIRPS. WAILS)

790
00:31:24.640 --> 00:31:27.280
<i>(RADIO CHATTER)</i>

791
00:31:27.280 --> 00:31:28.620
I'm a cop. I was ju...

792
00:31:28.620 --> 00:31:31.640
leaving your favorite
watering hole after shift?

793
00:31:31.640 --> 00:31:34.150
O'Neil's. right?

794
00:31:34.150 --> 00:31:37.030
License. registration and proof of insurance.

795
00:31:37.030 --> 00:31:39.000
You gotta be kidding me.

796
00:31:39.000 --> 00:31:41.630
(OPENS GLOVES BOX)

797
00:31:42.260 --> 00:31:46.800
Turn off the engine. Step out of the car for me.
(VEHICLES PASSING NEARBY)

798
00:31:46.800 --> 00:31:49.010
(GRUNTS)

799
00:31:53.000 --> 00:31:54.810
How much you have to drink tonight?

800
00:31:54.820 --> 00:31:57.290
- A couple of beers.
- What's a couple?

801
00:31:57.300 --> 00:32:00.480
Two? Twelve?

802
00:32:00.480 --> 00:32:03.820
I'm afraid we're gonna have
to do a field sobriety test.

803
00:32:03.820 --> 00:32:05.840
Legally. I can refuse that.

804
00:32:05.850 --> 00:32:08.180
And legally. I can throw you in jail.

805
00:32:08.180 --> 00:32:09.400
Objective symptoms.

806
00:32:09.400 --> 00:32:11.420
Glassy-eyed. smell like alcohol...

807
00:32:11.420 --> 00:32:15.010
since we being all by the book now.

808
00:32:15.020 --> 00:32:16.410
Follow the pen.

809
00:32:17.950 --> 00:32:19.940
You don't give a damn about a DUI.

810
00:32:19.940 --> 00:32:21.500
Careful. now.

811
00:32:21.500 --> 00:32:23.070
I've heard talking back to an officer

812
00:32:23.070 --> 00:32:24.700
is liable to get someone slammed up

813
00:32:24.700 --> 00:32:26.920
against the hood of a car. even cuffed.

814
00:32:26.920 --> 00:32:29.480
Listen. Sergeant. I didn't
know that was your family

815
00:32:29.480 --> 00:32:30.580
when we made the stop.

816
00:32:30.590 --> 00:32:32.250
Oh. they were lucky. then.

817
00:32:32.250 --> 00:32:34.170
Somebody else's family. and they could be

818
00:32:34.170 --> 00:32:35.920
making funeral arrangements right now.

819
00:32:35.930 --> 00:32:38.520
Walk and turn. You know the drill.

820
00:32:38.520 --> 00:32:41.670
<i>(RADIO CHATTER)</i>

821
00:32:41.670 --> 00:32:48.190
<i>♪ ♪</i>

822
00:32:55.350 --> 00:32:58.200
It was all a big misunderstanding.

823
00:32:58.210 --> 00:33:00.780
- I'm sorry if your family got...
- Keep your weak apology.

824
00:33:00.780 --> 00:33:02.210
Stand on one leg.

825
00:33:07.220 --> 00:33:09.540
Humiliating. isn't it?

826
00:33:09.540 --> 00:33:11.240
Being treated like a criminal.

827
00:33:11.240 --> 00:33:13.800
Singled out for no good reason.

828
00:33:13.800 --> 00:33:18.220
Harassed by a police officer
with questionable motives.

829
00:33:18.230 --> 00:33:19.710
I can report you.

830
00:33:19.710 --> 00:33:22.010
- This is retribution.
- If it was retribution.

831
00:33:22.010 --> 00:33:24.770
I would've done it when
your kids were in the car.

832
00:33:26.840 --> 00:33:28.880
I really am sorry. Sergeant.

833
00:33:31.570 --> 00:33:33.910
You have a nice night. then.

834
00:33:33.910 --> 00:33:37.910
<i>♪♪</i>

835
00:33:50.030 --> 00:33:53.030
♪♪

836
00:33:53.630 --> 00:33:56.030
(HYDRAULIC HISSING)

837
00:33:56.030 --> 00:33:58.030
(ENGINE SHUTS OFF)

838
00:33:59.630 --> 00:34:01.100
Okay. listen up.

839
00:34:01.100 --> 00:34:04.270
Last couple times we were
here. mistakes were made.

840
00:34:04.270 --> 00:34:05.780
That is not gonna happen again.

841
00:34:05.780 --> 00:34:07.580
(CARTS CLATTERING)

842
00:34:07.580 --> 00:34:10.520
That is why I am pairing
you up on your assignments.

843
00:34:10.520 --> 00:34:13.430
Eddie. Lena. you are on meats and deli.

844
00:34:13.430 --> 00:34:15.640
Nothing leaner than 92%.

845
00:34:15.640 --> 00:34:17.950
Hen. Chimney. baking aisle.

846
00:34:17.950 --> 00:34:19.980
Unrefined flour this time. Thank you.

847
00:34:19.980 --> 00:34:21.620
I will cover fruits and vegetables.

848
00:34:21.620 --> 00:34:23.360
Once you have everything on your list.

849
00:34:23.360 --> 00:34:25.270
we will reconvene at the dairy case.

850
00:34:25.280 --> 00:34:26.890
Let's move!

851
00:34:26.890 --> 00:34:29.650
This must be what the
invasion of Normandy felt like.

852
00:34:29.660 --> 00:34:31.280
(LAUGHS)

853
00:34:31.280 --> 00:34:33.470
What do you mean he
just dropped the charges?

854
00:34:33.470 --> 00:34:35.190
You make it sound like you're disappointed.

855
00:34:35.190 --> 00:34:37.900
Just surprised. Pleasantly.

856
00:34:39.500 --> 00:34:41.840
Apparently. that wasn't the
guy's first illegal fight.

857
00:34:41.840 --> 00:34:44.340
And they weighed that
against my service record...

858
00:34:44.350 --> 00:34:47.230
Captain America wins a
"Get Out of Jail Free Card"?

859
00:34:47.230 --> 00:34:49.020
And anyway. that jackass' knee surgery

860
00:34:49.020 --> 00:34:50.660
was three years ago.

861
00:34:50.660 --> 00:34:54.220
But not letting it go.
'Cause that's healthy.

862
00:34:54.220 --> 00:34:56.580
I just think Bobby needs to let go

863
00:34:56.580 --> 00:34:58.300
of being pissed off at Buck.

864
00:34:58.300 --> 00:35:00.440
I know that. and so does Bobby.

865
00:35:00.450 --> 00:35:01.800
How you figure?

866
00:35:01.810 --> 00:35:04.340
What do you think this whole
shopping trip is all about?

867
00:35:04.340 --> 00:35:06.380
- Buck.
- Exactly.

868
00:35:06.380 --> 00:35:08.570
It's just a distraction
to keep our minds off...

869
00:35:08.570 --> 00:35:10.530
No. no. no. Buck.

870
00:35:12.270 --> 00:35:16.320
Whoa. hey. uh. you guys. What's up?

871
00:35:16.320 --> 00:35:18.890
- What are you doing here?
- Me. I'm just here to...

872
00:35:18.900 --> 00:35:20.770
to do some... some shopping.

873
00:35:20.770 --> 00:35:22.570
Eight miles from your apartment?

874
00:35:22.570 --> 00:35:25.440
Yeah. well. this is the only place that has...

875
00:35:25.450 --> 00:35:27.390
Happy Cat laxative powder.

876
00:35:27.390 --> 00:35:30.670
You're buying cat laxative?

877
00:35:30.670 --> 00:35:34.210
Yeah. I've been thinking of. uh. of getting a cat.

878
00:35:34.210 --> 00:35:38.100
And you're anticipating your
new cat will be irregular.

879
00:35:38.100 --> 00:35:41.290
Um...

880
00:35:41.290 --> 00:35:44.610
Listen. I... I came here to apologize.

881
00:35:44.610 --> 00:35:46.990
Okay. I... I never
meant for things to get

882
00:35:46.990 --> 00:35:49.380
so out of hand with the lawsuit and...

883
00:35:49.390 --> 00:35:51.440
Yeah? What'd you think was gonna happen?

884
00:35:51.450 --> 00:35:53.650
The lawsuit's bad enough.
but you told your lawyer

885
00:35:53.650 --> 00:35:55.380
everything about us... personal things.

886
00:35:55.380 --> 00:35:58.140
You're supposed to be
truthful with your lawyer.

887
00:35:58.140 --> 00:35:59.600
Why are you so pissed at me?

888
00:35:59.600 --> 00:36:00.790
Because you're exhausting.

889
00:36:00.790 --> 00:36:01.940
We all have our own problems.

890
00:36:01.940 --> 00:36:03.440
but you don't see us whining about it.

891
00:36:03.440 --> 00:36:06.130
No. somehow. we just manage to suck it up.

892
00:36:06.130 --> 00:36:07.540
Why can't you?

893
00:36:07.540 --> 00:36:09.540
That's kinda harsh.
It's not like the guy asked

894
00:36:09.540 --> 00:36:11.020
to be crushed by a ladder truck.

895
00:36:11.020 --> 00:36:12.740
No. but he filed a stupid lawsuit.

896
00:36:12.740 --> 00:36:14.410
and now I can't even
talk to you because of it.

897
00:36:14.410 --> 00:36:16.530
You know how much
Christopher misses you?

898
00:36:16.530 --> 00:36:18.670
How could you? You're not around.

899
00:36:18.670 --> 00:36:20.000
- (PEOPLE ARGUING OUTSIDE)
- I... I didn't realize that.

900
00:36:20.000 --> 00:36:21.990
Maybe I can come and visit Christopher.

901
00:36:21.990 --> 00:36:23.460
You know the lawsuit doesn't prevent that.

902
00:36:23.460 --> 00:36:24.340
(ARGUING CONTINUES OUTSIDE)
No. it prevents me

903
00:36:24.340 --> 00:36:25.060
from reaching out to you.

904
00:36:25.060 --> 00:36:27.210
I couldn't even call you
to bail me out of jail.

905
00:36:28.590 --> 00:36:29.870
(MAN) You took my spot. man!

906
00:36:29.870 --> 00:36:31.820
If that was something that happened.

907
00:36:31.820 --> 00:36:34.470
What... What? What are you talking about?

908
00:36:34.470 --> 00:36:36.870
Look. man. why can't
you see my side of this?

909
00:36:36.880 --> 00:36:39.350
'Cause that's all you see.
(SHOUTING. CRASHING)

910
00:36:40.140 --> 00:36:41.980
(CRASHING)

911
00:36:41.980 --> 00:36:44.160
Someone should stop her.
(TIRES SCREECHING)

912
00:36:44.170 --> 00:36:45.910
- (WOMAN) Calm down.
- These two or those two?

913
00:36:45.910 --> 00:36:48.030
Let's go!
(HORN BLARING)

914
00:36:48.030 --> 00:36:50.190
(CRASHING)

915
00:36:50.200 --> 00:36:52.660
(TIRES SQUEALING. HORN HONKING)

916
00:36:52.660 --> 00:36:54.160
(MAN) Hey! Get back here!

917
00:36:54.160 --> 00:36:56.010
(SIREN WAILS)

918
00:36:56.010 --> 00:36:59.040
<i>(THRILLING MUSIC)</i>

919
00:36:59.040 --> 00:37:01.920
<i>♪ ♪</i>

920
00:37:01.930 --> 00:37:03.520
(SHOUTING)

921
00:37:03.520 --> 00:37:05.190
(HORN HONKING)

922
00:37:05.190 --> 00:37:06.810
Eddie. Lena. get the tools.

923
00:37:06.810 --> 00:37:08.840
Hen. Chimney. check on the drivers.

924
00:37:08.840 --> 00:37:11.860
(HORN HONKING)

925
00:37:11.860 --> 00:37:14.780
(SHOUTING. HONKING)

926
00:37:17.170 --> 00:37:19.390
(HORN HONKS)

927
00:37:28.970 --> 00:37:30.470
Hey.

928
00:37:32.860 --> 00:37:35.410
Karen? What's wrong?

929
00:37:35.410 --> 00:37:38.050
The doctor called...

930
00:37:38.050 --> 00:37:41.750
and none of the embryos are good.

931
00:37:41.750 --> 00:37:46.560
Wh... What? We had six. None?

932
00:37:46.560 --> 00:37:49.560
(CLEARS THROAT) It's just that they had. uh.

933
00:37:49.560 --> 00:37:54.640
chromosomal abnormalities or defects.

934
00:37:54.640 --> 00:37:56.780
They have to be discarded.

935
00:37:56.780 --> 00:37:58.780
♪♪

936
00:37:59.030 --> 00:38:01.740
She did say we can try again.

937
00:38:01.750 --> 00:38:04.600
Maybe do better next time.

938
00:38:04.600 --> 00:38:07.990
Okay. so... so we'll try again.

939
00:38:07.990 --> 00:38:09.920
But what if it fails again?

940
00:38:09.920 --> 00:38:12.660
I should've frozen my
eggs when I was younger.

941
00:38:12.660 --> 00:38:14.610
but I just kept thinking there was time.

942
00:38:14.610 --> 00:38:16.240
No. don't... don't do this.

943
00:38:16.240 --> 00:38:18.580
Don't put this on yourself. Karen.

944
00:38:18.580 --> 00:38:20.410
But it is on me. (SIGHS)

945
00:38:20.410 --> 00:38:22.760
- I'm so sorry. (SNIFFLES)
- No. no.

946
00:38:22.760 --> 00:38:25.340
No. this is not your fault.

947
00:38:25.340 --> 00:38:28.920
- You did everything exactly right.
- (KAREN SOBBING)

948
00:38:28.920 --> 00:38:31.920
Every test. every treatment.

949
00:38:31.920 --> 00:38:34.920
Every doctor's order. you followed it to the letter.

950
00:38:34.930 --> 00:38:37.760
Yeah. and my body has been fighting me

951
00:38:37.760 --> 00:38:40.600
every step of the way.

952
00:38:40.600 --> 00:38:42.390
Fighting me. (SNIFFLES)

953
00:38:42.390 --> 00:38:44.860
The IVF. the IUI.

954
00:38:44.860 --> 00:38:48.310
the complications and the side effects. and...

955
00:38:48.310 --> 00:38:51.750
It's... It's trying to tell me something.

956
00:38:53.460 --> 00:38:55.990
Give up.

957
00:38:55.990 --> 00:38:59.040
- Maybe I should listen.
- No.

958
00:38:59.040 --> 00:39:01.130
(SOBS)

959
00:39:01.140 --> 00:39:04.970
- I'm sorry.
- No. No.

960
00:39:04.970 --> 00:39:09.810
- (KAREN) I'm so sorry.
- (HEN) Don't be.

961
00:39:09.810 --> 00:39:12.150
Don't be.

962
00:39:12.150 --> 00:39:14.150
(LOW HUM OF CHAT)

963
00:39:14.150 --> 00:39:16.150
(PAPER RUSTLING)

964
00:39:17.160 --> 00:39:19.390
Sergeant Grant?

965
00:39:19.390 --> 00:39:21.870
I... I'm Officer Andrew Martin.

966
00:39:21.880 --> 00:39:23.420
I was on the scene the other night

967
00:39:23.420 --> 00:39:24.640
for your family's traffic stop.

968
00:39:24.640 --> 00:39:26.350
Oh. yeah.

969
00:39:26.350 --> 00:39:28.330
I'm familiar with your work.

970
00:39:28.330 --> 00:39:30.240
I just want you to know how sorry I am.

971
00:39:30.240 --> 00:39:32.390
I... I didn't see your son in the backseat.

972
00:39:32.390 --> 00:39:35.000
And then it was instinct.

973
00:39:35.000 --> 00:39:36.670
A bad one.

974
00:39:36.670 --> 00:39:38.180
When we say "protect and serve."

975
00:39:38.180 --> 00:39:42.030
we mean the community. not ourselves.

976
00:39:42.030 --> 00:39:44.300
I remember being a rookie.

977
00:39:44.300 --> 00:39:46.680
The nerves. not knowing
what you're walking up on.

978
00:39:46.680 --> 00:39:48.430
not sure what to do when you get there.

979
00:39:48.430 --> 00:39:51.540
It's natural to follow your partner's lead.

980
00:39:51.540 --> 00:39:54.230
Just don't follow it off a cliff.

981
00:39:54.230 --> 00:39:59.050
<i>♪ ♪</i>

982
00:39:59.050 --> 00:40:00.860
Do better.

983
00:40:00.860 --> 00:40:04.680
<i>♪ ♪</i>

984
00:40:04.680 --> 00:40:06.850
(ROCK MUSIC PLAYING)
(BELL RINGING)

985
00:40:06.850 --> 00:40:09.890
So this is your idea of a team-building activity?

986
00:40:09.890 --> 00:40:12.060
(BOBBY) Well. trust falls are part of the job.

987
00:40:12.060 --> 00:40:15.120
I can't fix the world.
I can't offer some sage advice

988
00:40:15.120 --> 00:40:17.180
that's gonna make everything better.

989
00:40:17.180 --> 00:40:19.760
All I can offer is this.

990
00:40:19.760 --> 00:40:21.760
(GLASS SHATTERING)

991
00:40:21.760 --> 00:40:23.760
(OVERLAPPING CHATS)

992
00:40:24.550 --> 00:40:29.560
- I cannot believe you came.
- Rough day.

993
00:40:29.560 --> 00:40:32.730
I really need to break something right now.
(SHATTERING CONTINUES)

994
00:40:32.730 --> 00:40:34.710
What's that?

995
00:40:34.710 --> 00:40:36.920
Cap sprung for the deluxe package.

996
00:40:36.920 --> 00:40:38.470
Full minibar!

997
00:40:38.470 --> 00:40:40.730
They serve alcohol in this place?

998
00:40:40.740 --> 00:40:43.650
Oh. yeah. I'm surprised
we don't get more calls from here.

999
00:40:45.390 --> 00:40:48.410
Well. it looks like you have
some more team building to do.

1000
00:40:48.410 --> 00:40:50.200
(GLASS SHATTERS)

1001
00:40:51.450 --> 00:40:52.450
Yeah.

1002
00:40:55.420 --> 00:40:58.110
Hey. uh. hey. Bobby.

1003
00:40:58.110 --> 00:41:02.070
Thank you for... inviting me.

1004
00:41:02.070 --> 00:41:03.950
Look. I... I just wanted to apologize.

1005
00:41:03.950 --> 00:41:05.760
You're gonna get a call
tomorrow from the Chief.

1006
00:41:05.760 --> 00:41:07.450
You're being reinstated to active duty.

1007
00:41:07.450 --> 00:41:09.340
The brass didn't want the headache.

1008
00:41:09.340 --> 00:41:11.120
They're afraid of the bad press.

1009
00:41:11.120 --> 00:41:13.780
Well... (LAUGHS) That... That's awesome.

1010
00:41:13.780 --> 00:41:15.790
Yeah. maybe not.

1011
00:41:15.800 --> 00:41:17.630
They gave me the option to transfer you.

1012
00:41:17.630 --> 00:41:19.760
They understood
how I might not want you back

1013
00:41:19.760 --> 00:41:21.260
after everything you put us through.

1014
00:41:21.260 --> 00:41:22.780
But I said no.

1015
00:41:22.780 --> 00:41:24.610
You're coming back to the 118

1016
00:41:24.610 --> 00:41:28.100
where I can keep an eye on you.
(OBJECTS CRASHING)

1017
00:41:28.100 --> 00:41:29.690
Thanks. Captain. (CLAPS HANDS)

1018
00:41:29.690 --> 00:41:31.980
- You won't regret it.
- You might.

1019
00:41:31.980 --> 00:41:34.620
My house. my rules. Remember that?

1020
00:41:34.620 --> 00:41:39.630
♪ BISHOP BRIGGS' ♪
♪ "WHITE FLAG" PLAYS ♪

1021
00:41:39.630 --> 00:41:41.650
<i>(EDDIE) Rage is defined as an intense</i>

1022
00:41:41.650 --> 00:41:43.570
<i>or violent type of anger.</i>

1023
00:41:43.580 --> 00:41:44.990
(SCREAMS)

1024
00:41:44.990 --> 00:41:47.300
<i>♪ Ohh ♪</i>

1025
00:41:47.300 --> 00:41:51.880
<i>(EDDIE) Road rage. office rage.
even airplane rage.</i>

1026
00:41:51.880 --> 00:41:53.810
<i>♪ This time I won't let go ♪</i>

1027
00:41:53.810 --> 00:41:55.490
<i>(EDDIE) Seems like the whole world</i>

1028
00:41:55.490 --> 00:41:57.720
<i>is on the edge of snapping lately.</i>

1029
00:41:57.720 --> 00:42:00.800
<i>But it's not the only way we use that word.</i>

1030
00:42:00.800 --> 00:42:03.300
<i>A raging fire.</i>

1031
00:42:03.300 --> 00:42:06.010
